{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":890,"text":"Growing up, I didn't always understand"},{"time":3190,"text":"why my parents made me\nfollow the rules that they did."},{"time":5885,"text":"Like, why did I really \nhave to mow the lawn?"},{"time":8675,"text":"Why was homework really that important?"},{"time":11343,"text":"Why couldn't I put jelly beans \nin my oatmeal?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":15267,"text":"My childhood was abound\nwith questions like this."},{"time":18123,"text":"Normal things about being a kid\nand realizing that sometimes,"},{"time":22396,"text":"it was best to listen to my parents\neven when I didn't exactly understand why."},{"time":26479,"text":"And it's not that they didn't want\nme to think critically."},{"time":29495,"text":"Their parenting always sought \nto reconcile the tension"},{"time":32096,"text":"between having my siblings and I\nunderstand the realities of the world,"},{"time":35547,"text":"while ensuring that we never accepted\nthe status quo as inevitable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39654,"text":"I came to realize that this,\nin and of itself,"},{"time":42964,"text":"was a very purposeful form of education."},{"time":46050,"text":"One of my favorite educators,\nBrazilian author and scholar Paulo Freire,"},{"time":50170,"text":"speaks quite explicitly\nabout the need for education"},{"time":53269,"text":"to be used as a tool for critical \nawakening and shared humanity."},{"time":57857,"text":"In his most famous book,\n\"Pedagogy of the Oppressed,\""},{"time":60642,"text":"he states, \"No one can be \nauthentically human"},{"time":65156,"text":"while he prevents others from being so.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":68167,"text":"I've been thinking a lot about this \nlately, this idea of humanity,"},{"time":71987,"text":"and specifically, who in this world\nis afforded the privilege"},{"time":75264,"text":"of being perceived as fully human."},{"time":78280,"text":"Over the course of \nthe past several months,"},{"time":80610,"text":"the world has watched\nas unarmed black men, and women,"},{"time":83818,"text":"have had their lives taken\nat the hands of police and vigilante."},{"time":87755,"text":"These events and all that \nhas transpired after them"},{"time":90648,"text":"have brought me back to my own childhood"},{"time":92756,"text":"and the decisions that my parents made\nabout raising a black boy in America"},{"time":97100,"text":"that growing up, I didn't always\nunderstand in the way that I do now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101977,"text":"I think of how hard it must have been,\nhow profoundly unfair it must have felt"},{"time":106212,"text":"for them to feel like they had \nto strip away parts of my childhood"},{"time":110409,"text":"just so that I could come home at night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113210,"text":"For example, I think of how one night,"},{"time":115311,"text":"when I was around 12 years old, on an\novernight field trip to another city,"},{"time":119213,"text":"my friends and I bought Super Soakers"},{"time":121559,"text":"and turned the hotel parking lot\ninto our own water-filled battle zone."},{"time":126102,"text":"We hid behind cars,"},{"time":127805,"text":"running through the darkness that\nlay between the streetlights,"},{"time":130973,"text":"boundless laughter ubiquitous \nacross the pavement."},{"time":134384,"text":"But within 10 minutes,"},{"time":136467,"text":"my father came outside, \ngrabbed me by my forearm"},{"time":139480,"text":"and led me into our room\nwith an unfamiliar grip."},{"time":142505,"text":"Before I could say anything,"},{"time":144369,"text":"tell him how foolish he had \nmade me look in front of my friends,"},{"time":147727,"text":"he derided me for being so naive."},{"time":150842,"text":"Looked me in the eye, \nfear consuming his face,"},{"time":155385,"text":"and said, \"Son, I'm sorry,"},{"time":157930,"text":"but you can't act the same \nas your white friends."},{"time":160967,"text":"You can't pretend to shoot guns."},{"time":163202,"text":"You can't run around in the dark."},{"time":165088,"text":"You can't hide behind anything\nother than your own teeth.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":168132,"text":"I know now how scared he must have been,"},{"time":171135,"text":"how easily I could have fallen\ninto the empty of the night,"},{"time":175148,"text":"that some man would mistake this water"},{"time":177907,"text":"for a good reason to wash\nall of this away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181134,"text":"These are the sorts of messages I've been\ninundated with my entire life:"},{"time":184546,"text":"Always keep your hands where they \ncan see them, don't move too quickly,"},{"time":188045,"text":"take off your hood when the sun goes down."},{"time":190116,"text":"My parents raised me and my siblings\nin an armor of advice,"},{"time":193223,"text":"an ocean of alarm bells so someone\nwouldn't steal the breath from our lungs,"},{"time":196854,"text":"so that they wouldn't make\na memory of this skin."},{"time":199166,"text":"So that we could be kids, \nnot casket or concrete."},{"time":201674,"text":"And it's not because they thought it\nwould make us better than anyone else"},{"time":205154,"text":"it's simply because they wanted \nto keep us alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207672,"text":"All of my black friends were raised\nwith the same message,"},{"time":210402,"text":"the talk, given to us \nwhen we became old enough"},{"time":212679,"text":"to be mistaken for a nail ready\nto be hammered to the ground,"},{"time":215624,"text":"when people made our melanin\nsynonymous with something to be feared."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220118,"text":"But what does it do to a child"},{"time":222591,"text":"to grow up knowing that you\ncannot simply be a child?"},{"time":226041,"text":"That the whims of adolescence\nare too dangerous for your breath,"},{"time":229190,"text":"that you cannot simply be curious,"},{"time":230854,"text":"that you are not afforded the luxury\nof making a mistake,"},{"time":233548,"text":"that someone's implicit bias"},{"time":235316,"text":"might be the reason you don't\nwake up in the morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238156,"text":"But this cannot be what defines us."},{"time":239871,"text":"Because we have parents\nwho raised us to understand"},{"time":242462,"text":"that our bodies weren't meant\nfor the backside of a bullet,"},{"time":245238,"text":"but for flying kites and jumping rope,\nand laughing until our stomachs burst."},{"time":248872,"text":"We had teachers who taught us \nhow to raise our hands in class,"},{"time":251856,"text":"and not just to signal surrender,"},{"time":253424,"text":"and that the only thing we should give up"},{"time":255390,"text":"is the idea that we \naren't worthy of this world."},{"time":257763,"text":"So when we say that black lives matter,\nit's not because others don't,"},{"time":261043,"text":"it's simply because we must affirm that we\nare worthy of existing without fear,"},{"time":264751,"text":"when so many things tell us we are not."},{"time":266877,"text":"I want to live in a world where my son"},{"time":268839,"text":"will not be presumed guilty\nthe moment he is born,"},{"time":271327,"text":"where a toy in his hand isn't mistaken\nfor anything other than a toy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275178,"text":"And I refuse to accept that we can't\nbuild this world into something new,"},{"time":278613,"text":"some place where a child's name"},{"time":280110,"text":"doesn't have to be written \non a t-shirt, or a tombstone,"},{"time":282857,"text":"where the value of someone's life"},{"time":284474,"text":"isn't determined by anything other \nthan the fact that they had lungs,"},{"time":288273,"text":"a place where every single \none of us can breathe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292491,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293445,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}